title: PCM goes 1-4 at Pella tourney
text:
PCM goes 1-4 at Pella tourney Published: Tuesday, Oct. 13, 2015 10:54 a.m. CDT By Troy Hyde Newton Daily News 
PELLA — The Prairie City-Monroe volleyball team traveled to Pella on Saturday and came home with a 1-4 mark in five matches. 
The Mustangs’ lone win came against Knoxville in straight sets, but they lost to Greene County and North Mahaska in three and were swept by Mediapolis and host Pella. 
PCM defeated Knoxville 21-9, 21-13. Leading the way for the Mustangs was Ashley Van Gorp, who finished with five kills and 10 digs. Kayla Jennings had 11 assists, five digs and she was 19-for-19 in serves. 
Greene County defeated the Mustangs 16-21, 22-20, 15-10. In that match, Regan Olson had six kills and was 11-of-12 in serves. Van Gorp added eight digs, while Jennings dished out 16 assists. 
North Mahaska defeated PCM 21-18, 14-21, 15-12. Van Gorp had eight kills, Katie VandeWall contributed four kills and Jennings finished with 18 assists. Jennings was 9-of-10 in serves with two aces and Tatum Nearmyer collected eight digs. 
The Dutch downed PCM 21-7, 21-14. Kaylee Townsend had a team-high three kills, while Nearmyer had five digs and Jennings delivered nine assists. 
Mediapolis swept PCM 21-17, 21-11. Van Gorp led the way with four kills and six digs, while Jennings collected 10 assists, two kills and was 7-of-7 in serves. 
PCM (8-22) plays in its final home match of the season at about 7:30 p.m. Thursday against Roland-Story.
